               That Ieſus Chriſt was deſcribed in their ſight, and among them crucified. His meaning is that Chriſte was ſo liuely preached to them, as his liuely Image was ſet before their eyes, or els had been crucified amongſt them. This is the power of preaching, this is the duetie of the Miniſter, plainly and effectually to diſcribe and ſet forth the merite of Chriſt his Paſſion, ſo that it maie bee ſeen as it were before the eyes.
